## 🔄 The `uv` Workflow (always inside `nix develop`)

```bash
uv sync                 # (1st time or change, handled by shellHook)
uv add requests         # update deps
uv add --dev pytest     # dev deps
source .venv/bin/activate
uv run pytest           # runs anywhere, venv or not
```

---

## 🧪 devShell Quality Checklist

- [ ] `flake.nix` uses `flake-parts` and targets all 4 platforms.
- [ ] Only add Python interpreter (`python3XX`) & `uv` in shell.
- [ ] gitignore `.venv`, commit `uv.lock`.
- [ ] No `buildInputs`/`withPackages`/`with`/legacy `shell.nix`.
- [ ] `shellHook` only idempotently runs `uv sync`.
- [ ] All system library deps are platform-guarded.
- [ ] `nix flake check` + `nix develop` work OOTB.

---

## 🐞 Debugging lib issues

- If Python install fails, find missing .so with:
  ```
  nix-locate -w libfoo.so
  ```
  …then add the matching `pkgs.*` lib to your `packages`.

---

## 🚦 Deviation Allowed?
- Only for upstream `nixpkgs` contributions or explicitly grandfathered legacy projects.
- Otherwise: **flakes required, always.**

